# Slider — React API

## Props
```tsx
interface SliderProps {
  value: number;
  onChange: (value: number) => void;
  min?: number;          // default: 0
  max?: number;          // default: 100
  step?: number;         // default: 1
  disabled?: boolean;    // default: false
  showValue?: boolean;   // show current value label
  showTicks?: boolean;   // show tick marks
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';  // default: 'md'
  className?: string;
  'aria-label'?: string;
  'aria-labelledby'?: string;
}
```

## Behaviour
- Pointer capture for drag (works on touch and mouse)
- Snaps to nearest `step` value
- Full keyboard support: Arrow (±step), Page (±10%), Home/End
- `role="slider"`, `aria-valuemin/max/now`, `aria-disabled` on thumb

## Usage
```tsx
const [val, setVal] = useState(50);
<Slider
  value={val}
  onChange={setVal}
  min={0}
  max={100}
  step={5}
  showValue
  aria-label="Coverage amount"
/>
```
